This paper deals with the transformation of context-free grammars, which is a common topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses probabilistic grammars, which are often used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of factorization in the paper suggests a focus on algorithmic efficiency, which is relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's discussion of grammar size and complexity could also be relevant to software engineering and programming languages (cs.SE).
